text:
Pro-ana, bodybuilding, trans, and incel communities are shockingly similar if you delve into them. One pinnacle of each being body dysmorphia. 

Most niche internet spaces are closely aligned to at least one of these communities.

This sentence at the middle of your article: 

"people who become addicted to a certain ‘vibe’ or ‘atmosphere’/are in an endless feedback loop of building and sharing mood boards or images to people who seriously self-harm." 

really cuts to the core of it, I think.
